gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 101, Nets 86
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Brooklyn, 101-86. For Minnesota, Anthony Edwards led the way with 29 points, eight rebounds, and 2 steals aided by Karl Anthony-Towns recording 28 points (four 3PM), nine rebounds, four assists, and two blocks. Cam Thomas led the way with 18 points and six rebounds while Mikal Bridges tallied 15 points, six rebounds, and eight assists for Brooklyn in the losing effort. Minnesota wins and improves to 40-17, while Brooklyn moves to 21-35 in the loss.
